'''Alan Mulholland''' is a [[Gaelic football]] [[Manager (Gaelic games)|manager]], who was senior manager of [[Galway GAA|Galway]], from 2011 to 2014 having previously been Minor & U21 manager.
During his playing career Mulholland earned no national honours as the county teams of Galway failed to reach a single All-Ireland Final. In 2007, Mulholland guided [[Galway GAA|Galway]] to the [[All-Ireland Minor Football Championship]] beating [[Derry GAA|Derry]], as well as guiding them to the U21 Final in which they defeated [[Cavan GAA|Cavan]] in May 2011. On 3 October 2011, Mulholland was appointed as the [[Galway GAA|Galway]] senior football manager, replacing [[Tomás Ó Flatharta]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rte.ie/sport/gaa/championship/2011/1004/mulhollanda_galway.html |title=Mulholland takes control of Galway football |work=RTÉ Sport |date=4 October 2011 |accessdate=4 October 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111008010058/http://www.rte.ie/sport/gaa/championship/2011/1004/mulhollanda_galway.html |archivedate=8 October 2011 |df= }}</ref>
