'''COFEPOSA''' or the '''Conservation of Foreign Exchange and Prevention of Smuggling Activities Act''' is an [[Act of Indian|Act]] of the [[Parliament]] passed in [[1974 in India|1974]] during  administration of [[Indira Gandhi]], trying to [[Foreign exchange controls|retain foreign currency]] and prevent [[smuggling]]. It was an economic adjunct to the controversial [[Maintenance of Internal Security Act]] (MISA) which was enacted in 1971. Though MISA repealed in 1978, the law never was.<ref name="HardingHatchard1993">{{cite book|last1=Harding|first1=Andrew|last2=Hatchard|first2=John|title=Preventive Detention and Security Law: A Comparative Survey|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=J0eBd0JDvRQC&pg=PA61|year=1993|publisher=Martinus Nijhoff Publishers|isbn=0-7923-2432-3|pages=61–}}</ref>

