A '''feeder line''' is a secondary [[assembly line]] which provides parts for use in a [[Assembly line|primary assembly line]]. Researchers assert that the traditional level scheduling [[methodology]] of [[assembly line]] planning is not effective unless feeder lines provide parts to the primary assembly line.

