[[File:Neda logo.jpg|thumb|200px|Logo of the National Electronic Distributors Association]]
The '''National Electronic Distributors Association''' ('''NEDA''') was a [[trade association]] in the [[United States of America|United States]] of manufacturers and distributors.<ref>[http://www.nedassoc.org National Electronic Distributors Association | The Voice of Authorized Distribution<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070707220302/http://www.nedassoc.org/ |date=2007-07-07 }}</ref>

The association cooperates in standardization of names for components, such as batteries.<ref>[http://www.nedassoc.org/roundtable.php5 NEDA Roundtables] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090323233945/http://www.nedassoc.org/roundtable.php5 |date=2009-03-23 }}</ref> NEDA is often cited by American manufacturers, along with [[American National Standards Institute|ANSI]], for names of components.{{Citation needed|date=October 2007}}

NEDA merged with the [[Electronic Industries Alliance]] in 2010 to form the Electronic Components Industry Association (ECIA).<ref>[http://www.edn.com/electronics-news/4311980/NEDA-ECA-merge-target-counterfeit-components   NEDA, ECA merge, target counterfeit components]</ref>

